<H1>ICS 1C HW 4 for Scott Phillips</H1></a>
<H2>The Current Situation in Chechnya</H2>
Name:<B> Scott Phillips</B><br>
E-mail: <code>eaaa074@ea.oac.uci.edu</code><br>
<H3>Useful Sights</H3>
<p>These are some of the sights that I was able to use for research.  The 
majority of the articles that I have found I mailed to myself for quicker 
reference and more reliability.  I found that as I attempted to return to 
previous articles, many times they had been replaced.  The links below 
very likely contain pertinent information, but not the original 
information that I encountered.<p>
 <UL>
<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.undp.org/11/uncurr">United Nations Current 
Highlights</A>
<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.voa.gov/11/pub/radio/newswire">Voice Of America 
News and English Broadcasts Wire Service</A>
<LI><A 
HREF="gopher://gopher.enews.com:2100/77/search/Index/index?Chechnya">
Enews Contents and Articles</A>

<LI><A HREF="http://query1.lycos.cs.cmu.edu/cgi-bin/pursuit?Chechnya">A 
Lycos 
Query regarding Chechnya</A> This should bring out the most up-to-date 
news available.
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nando.net/newsroom/nt/world.html">The Nando 
Times</A> can have significant articles regarding to Chechnya 
<LI><A HREF="http://www.bbcnc.org.uk/online/oneworld/top.html">The BBC 
Oneworld page</A> is a link to updated news in many different forms
<LI><A HREF="http://193.6.96.40/kum.htm">Publications of the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs</A> contains interesting statements on many different 
regions of the world
<LI><A HREF="http://solar.rtd.utk.edu/friends/home.html">Friends and 
Partners</A> is a joint venture between citizens of both the U.S. and 
Russia including a variety of information sources.  Possibly one of the 
best overall references that I have ever seen.
<LI><A HREF="http://www.pitt.edu/~cjp/rees.html">The World-Wide Web 
Virtual Library: Russian and East European Studies</A> page contains more 
information than one could feasably search through.  It contains links 
that are very helpful
<LI><A 
HREF="http://solar.rtd.utk.edu/friends/news/chechnya/master.html">
Chechnya News</A> is a link off of the Friends and Partners that is a
very complete reference to what is happening and has happened so far.
</UL> 
